      "writtenOn": "2021-06-03T17:59:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wrote a new test, added some logging to BiosService, and could not see those logs.  So I added lots of logging everywhere, and passed the stderr down into newRemoteLoggingServer() so that remoteLoggingServer.Log could write the log message to stderr as well as the s.inbox.  And I saw my log messages.\n\nThe behavior I saw in the remoteLoggingClient was that it would call newRemoteLoggingClient and then immediately the goroutine calling st.Recv() would exit. I think it was getting the EOF, because I was logging all the other errors and there was none.\n\nI deleted all that excess logging, and moved on because I got the issue worked out that I was trying to do all the logging for in the first place resolved.\n\nBut for that test, I still never get any remote logs at all.\n\nIt all seems overly complex, just capturing stderr, and not using the remote logging grpc at all would be much simpler.",
